{
  "category": "Uncategorized",
  "description": "We need a way for the end user to be able to have more visibility into all the actions that are performed. I think one of the ways we could do this is by creating a new page called the activity feed. As actions are performed, new items would be added to the activity feed. This would allow the user to see exactly what happens when, for example:\n- a new email comes in\n- the outlet is connected\n- a new rule moves an email into a folder\n- someone creates a new page\n- a new smart rule is triggered, etc.\nThink through all the core cases where a user would want to see what action is being performed, and then create a well-designed activity page that would be a vertical scrolling where someone can see all the different activities that are performed.",
  "title": "Create activity feed to track user actions",
